{"TopicId":126293,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"Kerbfleet: A Jool Odyssey-CHAPTER 21 pg 28--and the answer to Angelo\u0026#039;s question is...","CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-23T21:47:39Z","PageNum":138,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"max_creative","CreatedById":159640,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T01:51:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222693353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469636105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I am going to address that issue in the comic...as you\u0027ll see, I\u0027m already doing enough damage to the walls \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWalls? What walls? I don\u0027t even have fourth walls!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLinus: And I have a bunch of Yummy Mint Ice- SURFACE SAMPLES!!! YEAH! SURFACE SAMPLES!!! I was totally not just eating our surface samples!\u00A0I was uhhhh... Erm... Checking if these Pol surface samples are real Gold? Because Pol is Yellow?...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWalt: You were eating the surface samples.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv data-role=\u0022contentPage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLinus: NO I- ok fine. Yes I was...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T01:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222693353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469636105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo yeah, I decided to turn terrain scatter on. The spiky things just look too awesome for me \u003Cem\u003Enot \u003C/em\u003Eto! I had it off in 1.0.5 because of performance issues, but of course that\u0027s all in the past now that we\u0027re \u0027turbocharged\u0027 in 1.1. I only wish I\u0027d thought to do it before the \u003Cem\u003EIntrepid \u003C/em\u003Elanding, that would have made it look even more spectacular!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was trying really hard and be polite and not mention it, but heck yeah, you HAVE to turn the scatter on when your on Pol...\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s by far the best terrain scatter in the game!\u00A0 I\u0027m just amazed one didn\u0027t sprout right thru the Intrepid!\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-28T02:00:02Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2016 02:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceplaneAddict","CreatedById":149322,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T03:28:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Kuzzter, if the wheels say they\u0027re not blocked, try what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69507-geschosskopf/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002269507\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/69507-geschosskopf/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Geschosskopf\u003C/a\u003E said, or maybe try Infinite Electricity, even tho the electric capacity may be at full.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T15:17:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694195\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469676488\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149322\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceplaneAddict\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, SpaceplaneAddict said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Kuzzter, if the wheels say they\u0027re not blocked, try what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/69507-geschosskopf/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002269507\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/69507-geschosskopf/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Geschosskopf\u003C/a\u003E said, or maybe try Infinite Electricity, even tho the electric capacity may be at full.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAppreciate the help from both of you, thanks--looks like the wheels are \u003Cem\u003Enot \u003C/em\u003Eblocked, as the replacement rover (identical one spawned on Kerbin and hyperedited to Pol) works just fine:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022qP9e1HK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/qP9e1HK.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the best current hypothesis is that the rover wheels\u00A0originally spawned in 1.0.x just don\u0027t work in 1.1.x. I\u0027ve posted a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/144608-rovemax-m1-wheels-wont-drive-rover-on-pol/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EQuestion on the subject\u003C/a\u003E in the appropriate section, and there is a link there to a .sfs file with both rovers if anyone is interested in debugging the problem. But for purposes of our story here, the problem is solved \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-28T15:18:18Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2016 03:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kuzzter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceplaneAddict","CreatedById":149322,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T16:10:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh hey! Kuzzter, \u0027gratz on 9k rep!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wildcat111","CreatedById":165926,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T17:09:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222691726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469544403\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2016-07-26 at 8:46 AM, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSarge has been holding down the \u0027W\u0027 key for a while now and the rover doesn\u0027t move. He really, really wants to explore, especially since those strange spiky things suddenly popped up out of the ground for no apparent reason.\u00A0I understand wheels might be bugged now--any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe wheels are very stubborn on Pol?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-29T17:13:18Z\u0022 title=\u002207/29/2016 05:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Wildcat111\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alchemist","CreatedById":8825,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T18:37:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696239\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469812185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165926\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wildcat111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Wildcat111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe wheels are very stubborn on Pol?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh, I once landed a large rover on Gilly. Let\u0027s just say it still used nukes to actually move around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wildcat111","CreatedById":165926,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T18:45:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696356\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469817468\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00228825\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alchemist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Alchemist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh, I once landed a large rover on Gilly. Let\u0027s just say it still used nukes to actually move around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E. got me laughing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222691726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469544403\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2016-07-26 at 8:46 AM, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSarge has been holding down the \u0027W\u0027 key for a while now and the rover doesn\u0027t move. He really, really wants to explore, especially since those strange spiky things suddenly popped up out of the ground for no apparent reason.\u00A0I understand wheels might be bugged now--any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe you should use a hovercraft with ion engines?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-29T18:45:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/29/2016 06:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Wildcat111\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:02:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696377\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469817918\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165926\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wildcat111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Wildcat111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe you should use a hovercraft with ion engines?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou did see the part where I said I got the rover working, right? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:03:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022111501\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kuzzter\u003C/a\u003E, maybe it\u0027s time to get out the agonizer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469822608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022111501\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kuzzter\u003C/a\u003E, maybe it\u0027s time to get out the agonizer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, I\u0027ll just make it canon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/CFIQBgm.png\u0022 alt=\u0022CFIQBgm.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/OSUWAD3.png\u0022 alt=\u0022OSUWAD3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDriving is somewhat challenging, but loads of fun. On\u00A0level ground I can get the rover up to about 10 m/s... of course any bump will get you airborne and heaven help you if you attempt to turn. There\u0027s a reaction wheel right in front of the docking port,\u00A0I tend to drive with the dialogue box for it open so I can quickly turn it on whenever I need to re-orient the wheels towards the ground (have been too lazy to remap the keyboard, so WASD handles both rover controls and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E right now--reaction wheel is off when driving, otherwise stepping on the accelerator would flip it over) And yes, I see that there\u0027s an \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E Only\u0022 option on the reaction wheels now but I haven\u0027t bothered figuring that out yet, I\u0027m too busy making screenshots and word balloons \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that\u0027s Pod Racing... or Pol Roving... or something like that.... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:40:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll your rover needs now is a Confederate flag and a horn that plays the first twelve notes of \u0027Dixie\u0027...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: sorry, didn\u0027t even look at the title of the episode....\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-29T20:45:12Z\u0022 title=\u002207/29/2016 08:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by UnusualAttitude\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:44:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469824813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UnusualAttitude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, UnusualAttitude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll your rover needs now is a Confederate flag and a horn that plays the first twelve notes of \u0027Dixie\u0027...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly, Forum rule 2.2e may preclude\u00A0the former, and vacuum the latter. Though I did once enter a replica \u002769 Dodge Charger called\u00A0\u0022Kerbal Lee\u0022 in a \u0022Dukes of Duna\u0022 driving challenge \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Torgo","CreatedById":149873,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:56:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut did Sarge slide across the hood before getting in?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wildcat111","CreatedById":165926,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T22:23:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696459\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469822531\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou did see the part where I said I got the rover working, right? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, i did. I was just making a suggestion for a future graphic novel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696487\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469823946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDriving is somewhat challenging, but loads of fun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats where the hoverboard comes in. It makes it more fun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geschosskopf","CreatedById":69507,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T00:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696487\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469823946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(have been too lazy to remap the keyboard, so WASD handles both rover controls and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E right now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI strongly recommend remapping the rover controls to the kepad. \u00A0That way, you can use WASD, the keypad, or both as the situation dictates. \u00A0KSP makes far too little use of the keypad so it\u0027s fair game for any remapping needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T00:52:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469839582\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269507\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geschosskopf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Geschosskopf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI strongly recommend remapping the rover controls to the kepad. \u00A0That way, you can use WASD, the keypad, or both as the situation dictates. \u00A0KSP makes far too little use of the keypad so it\u0027s fair game for any remapping needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh cool, I\u0027m not the only one that uses the keypad for roving!!!\u00A0\u00A0 Using the keypad to drive leaves your left hand free for thrusters, which my Chariots have, and also quite apparently so does Sarge\u0027s rover.\u00A0 It\u0027s much easier\u00A0using both hands\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-30T00:54:31Z\u0022 title=\u002207/30/2016 12:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geschosskopf","CreatedById":69507,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T00:58:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469839959\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s much easier\u00A0using both hands\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly, and no innuendos intended.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elowiny","CreatedById":117659,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T07:13:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wondering, what other bodies are you going to land the full \u003Cem\u003EIntrepid \u003C/em\u003Eon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rune","CreatedById":52690,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T08:33:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696487\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469823946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111501\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kuzzter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Kuzzter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a reaction wheel right in front of the docking port,\u00A0I tend to drive with the dialogue box for it open so I can quickly turn it on whenever I need to re-orient the wheels towards the ground (have been too lazy to remap the keyboard, so WASD handles both rover controls and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E right now--reaction wheel is off when driving, otherwise stepping on the accelerator would flip it over) And yes, I see that there\u0027s an \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E Only\u0022 option on the reaction wheels now but I haven\u0027t bothered figuring that out yet, I\u0027m too busy making screenshots and word balloons \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTaking the five minutes to map rover controls to IJKL will be the best expenditure of time you\u0027ll make this summer. And for the new versions, just copy-paste your settings file so you don\u0027t have to redo all the config options every update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRune. Just like docking, roving on low gravity is a two-hands-on-the-keyboard kind of thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-30T08:33:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/30/2016 08:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Rune\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"something","CreatedById":157505,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T09:38:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPol isn\u0027t made out of Pollen. Now I am really sad. Well I will redirect my Jool probe to Tylo. Maybe it is made out of tiles?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah keep up the great work \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022111501\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/111501-kuzzter/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kuzzter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T11:41:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469862787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117659\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elowiny\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Elowiny said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wondering, what other bodies are you going to land the full \u003Cem\u003EIntrepid \u003C/em\u003Eon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat makes you so sure the\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Efull\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intrepid is going to make it off Poll in one piece?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T13:24:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469862787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022117659\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elowiny\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Elowiny said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wondering, what other bodies are you going to land the full \u003Cem\u003EIntrepid \u003C/em\u003Eon?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot intending to land on any more--we\u0027ll lift off from Pol with the tanks filled, and should then have enough aboard for all the landing craft to do their jobs. Qwammer will refuel itself on Tylo and on Vall. Depending on the fuel situation I may land the ship on Pol one more time before heading for home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697144\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469867589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002252690\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rune\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Rune said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTaking the five minutes to map rover controls to IJKL will be the best expenditure of time you\u0027ll make this summer. And for the new versions, just copy-paste your settings file so you don\u0027t have to redo all the config options every update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, but then again I did activate thrusters and use IJKL to avoid spiky rock formations when Sarge and Melbe finished their Highlands survey and barrelled downhill back to \u003Cem\u003EIntrepid!\u00A0\u003C/em\u003EI\u0027ll figure something out, I\u0027m sure--there are a lot of keys on the keyboard to play with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697262\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469878906\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat makes you so sure the\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Efull\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intrepid is going to make it off Poll in one piece?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh. Well ,as far as we know the Kerbulans haven\u0027t arrived in the system yet. Pieces of the Intrepid are disappearing, though. We\u0027re down to one Jooldiver and a few scansats. I was thinking of firing a scansat from the surface to intercept Bop while we\u0027re waiting for the tanks to fill up; anything to shed part count!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"something","CreatedById":157505,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T18:53:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the communication satellite with these 4 tanks which allegedly contain \u0022fuel\u0022 did not arrive yet. Or did I miss an important part?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}